Graph where two adjacent nodes does not have same color.
For example Roll no1 and Rollno 2 does not have exactly same question paper.
But one thing more,where we can color the graph with just two color is called bipartitle graph.
Linear graph with no cycles is always a bipartitle graph.
Any graph with even cycle length is also a bipartite graph.
Any graph with odd cycle length can never be bipartite.
To find a cycle in a directed graph,
we generally use two arrays visited[] and pathvisited[].One is to track visited nodes and the other one is to track the current dfs
path visited nodes.
What is a safe node?
A node from which every possible path eventually leads to a termination node.(A node which has no outgoing edges).
There are two ways to find eventual safe state in graphs.
One is via dfs(If that node or any of it's neighbor is part of the cycle then it is not a safe state)
Another is via topo sort reverse the edges of graphs and then perform topo sort. Insert the elements one by one 
in the list as the indegree is becoming zero.)
